<%
  set_meta_tags(
    title: "Privacy Policy",
    description: "Privacy policy for jamesebentier.com — how we handle your email and consent data.",
  )
%>

<div class="py-16 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
  <p class="font-mono text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-primary mb-2">Legal</p>
  <h1 class="font-mono text-3xl mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>

  <div class="prose prose-base max-w-none text-base-content/80 space-y-6">
    <p>
      <strong>This page is a placeholder.</strong> A complete privacy policy will be published in a future update
      (see issue <a href="https://github.com/bitidev/jamesebentier.com/issues/1190" class="link link-primary" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">#1190</a>).
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-mono text-xl mt-8 mb-4">Newsletter sign-up</h2>
    <p>
      When you subscribe to the newsletter I collect your <strong>email address</strong> and the following
      consent metadata:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
      <li>The date and time you submitted the form (<em>consent_at</em>)</li>
      <li>Which page you signed up from (<em>consent_source</em>)</li>
      <li>A one-way cryptographic hash of your IP address — the raw IP is never stored</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Your email address is stored in our own database, not with a third-party email service provider.
      No email is sent until you confirm your address via the link in the confirmation email.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can unsubscribe at any time using the link included in every email.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-mono text-xl mt-8 mb-4">Site analytics</h2>
    <p>
      This site records <strong>anonymous page views</strong> in our own database — path, referrer,
      and optional campaign query parameters only. There are no third-party analytics trackers,
      no cookies for analytics, and no per-visitor IDs. Automated bot traffic is labeled separately
      from human visits so aggregates stay easy to read.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-mono text-xl mt-8 mb-4">Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For any data or privacy questions email
      <a href="mailto:james@jamesebentier.com" class="link link-primary">james@jamesebentier.com</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
